edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.device
Class XDLRCParser

java.lang.Object
  edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.device.XDLRCParser

public class XDLRCParser
extends java.lang.Object

This class is designed to parse the XDLRC files to create the compact device files used by XDL Tools. It also extracts the primitive definitions from the XDLRC. This parser is an improved version of the JavaCC parser which is no longer in use.

Author:
Chris Lavin Created on: Jul 7, 2010

parseXDLRC

public Device parseXDLRC(java.lang.String fileName,
                         boolean extractPrimitiveDefs)
Parses the XDLRC file specified by fileName and populates the Device and optionally the PrimitiveDefList based on extractPrimitiveDefs.

Parameters:
fileName - Name of the XDLRC file to parse.
extractPrimitiveDefs - A flag to indicate if the parser should extract and create the primitiveDefsList. This can be obtained through a getPrimitiveDefs() method after this method returns.
Returns:
The populated device.

getDevice

public Device getDevice()
Gets and returns the device. This should only be called after parseXDLRC() is first called.

Returns:
The device corresponding to this parser.

getPrimitiveDefs

public PrimitiveDefList getPrimitiveDefs()
Gets and returns the PrimitiveDefList. This should only be called after parseXDLRC() is first called.

Returns:
The Primitive definition list corresponding to this parser.
